        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 28 at 3:12PM CDT by NWS Bismarck ND</headline>
        <description>At 311 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 5
miles east of Grace City, or 21 miles northeast of Carrington, moving
east at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Grace City and Mchenry.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
